Even with delegates, C#&#x27;s version is pretty much equivalent to JS&#x27;s:<p>JavaScript:<p><pre><code>  var blah = function(){ return &quot;im a function&quot;};
</code></pre>
C# 3.0:<p><pre><code>  var blah = delegate { return &quot;im a function&quot;; };
</code></pre>
C# 2.0:<p><pre><code>  Func<string> blah = delegate { return &quot;im a function&quot;; };</code></pre>
